      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEW SHUFFLE (9) was far from disgraced when midfield to the flying Captains Mistress at Listed level in Sydney before making a winning return to this circuit, working before scoring by 2.7m. Tougher draw on the back row but he is capable. HES NO ROMEO NZ (5) was very good in a higher-graded race here last week, chasing the smart Captain Perfect for a 4.2m third. Draws wider but also comes back in grade and has a good record at this longer distance. SOAP AND BUBBLES (6) showed improvement when she came from the back row for a 2.8m third here last week. That added to a good record at this distance and she'll be peaking. CLYMENUS NZ (3) draws better than last week and had recorded a win and a placing the previous two times he raced here, both from back row draws.",
